At 05:11 24/09/2003, Zach Freshman wrote:
>In my futile attempt to get an accelerator pedal that won't stick, I think
>I've found a new wrench in the works. My acc. pedal hinge (
>http://www.busdepot.com/busdepot/details.jsp?partnumber=211721613 ) seems to
>be lifting off of the floor a bit. Not down where its welded, but where the
>curl is that holds the pin. This results in my pedal being turned too far to
>the right, thus throwing off all the linkage under the bus. Sounds good, eh
>:)

Mine was like that - after all sorts of attempts to bend it straight, it 
dawned on me that what was causing it to stick was the rubber cab mat 
sliding into the gap! A little local rubber surgery fixed it completely.

